defs.docs:
An implementation an encoder using [DEFLATE](http://www.gzip.org/zlib/rfc-deflate.html)
 compression algorightm in pure rust.

defs.name: Fast
defs.docs: Fast minimal compression (`CompressionOptions::fast()`).

defs.name: Default
defs.docs: Default level (`CompressionOptions::default()`).

defs.name: Best
defs.docs: Higher compression level (`CompressionOptions::high()`).

defs.name: Compression
defs.docs: An enum describing the level of compression to be used by the encoder

defs.name: Normal
defs.docs: Compress normally.

defs.name: _ForceFixed
defs.docs: Force fixed huffman tables. (Unimplemented!).

defs.name: _ForceStored
defs.docs: Force stored (uncompressed) blocks only. (Unimplemented!).

defs.name: SpecialOptions
defs.docs: Enum allowing some special options (not implemented yet)!

defs.name: CompressionOptions
defs.docs: A struct describing the options for a compressor or compression function.

defs.name: max_hash_checks
defs.docs: The maximum number of checks to make in the hash table for matches.

defs.name: lazy_if_less_than
defs.docs: Only lazy match if we have a length less than this value.

defs.name: matching_type
defs.docs: Whether to use lazy or greedy matching.

defs.name: special
defs.docs:
Force fixed/stored blocks (Not implemented yet).
 * Default value: `SpecialOptions::Normal`

defs.name: high
defs.docs: Returns compression settings rouhgly corresponding to the `HIGH(9)` setting in miniz.

defs.name: fast
defs.docs: Returns  a fast set of compression settings

defs.name: huffman_only
defs.docs:
Returns a set of compression settings that makes the compressor only compress using
 huffman coding. (Ignoring any length/distance matching)

defs.name: rle
defs.docs:
Returns a set of compression settings that makes the compressor compress only using
 run-length encoding (i.e only looking for matches one byte back).

defs.name: Greedy
defs.docs:
Use greedy matching: the matching algorithm simply uses a match right away
 if found.

defs.name: Lazy
defs.docs:
Use lazy matching: after finding a match, the next input byte is checked, to see
 if there is a better match starting at that byte.

defs.name: MatchingType
defs.docs: An enum describing whether we use lazy or greedy matching.

defs.name: DeflateEncoder
defs.docs: A DEFLATE encoder/compressor.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new encoder using the provided compression options.

defs.name: finish
defs.docs:
Encode all pending data to the contained writer, consume this `DeflateEncoder`,
 and return the contained writer if writing succeeds.

defs.name: reset
defs.docs:
Resets the encoder (except the compression options), replacing the current writer
 with a new one, returning the old one.

defs.name: ZlibEncoder
defs.docs: A Zlib encoder/compressor.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new `ZlibEncoder` using the provided compression options.

defs.name: finish
defs.docs:
Encode all pending data to the contained writer, consume this `ZlibEncoder`,
 and return the contained writer if writing succeeds.

defs.name: reset
defs.docs:
Resets the encoder (except the compression options), replacing the current writer
 with a new one, returning the old one.

defs.name: checksum
defs.docs: Return the adler32 checksum of the currently consumed data.

defs.name: write
defs.docs: Encoders implementing a `Write` interface.

defs.name: deflate_bytes_conf
defs.docs: Compress the given slice of bytes with DEFLATE compression.

defs.name: deflate_bytes
defs.docs:
Compress the given slice of bytes with DEFLATE compression using the default compression
 level.

defs.name: deflate_bytes_zlib_conf
defs.docs: Compress the given slice of bytes with DEFLATE compression, including a zlib header and trailer.

defs.name: deflate_bytes_zlib
defs.docs:
Compress the given slice of bytes with DEFLATE compression, including a zlib header and trailer,
 using the default compression level.
